    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="472"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9652</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Adviser on Political Relations</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-16">August 16,
                            1937</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: May I recommend that this matter<note
                        n="16" xml:id="d472fn16">See <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> be taken up urgently with the President.</p>
                <pb facs="0431" n="424" xml:id="pg_424"/>
                <p>May I suggest that if the President has any hesitation about authorizing the
                    sending of the 6th Marines, 1,200 men, from San Diego, an opportunity be given
                    for discussion of the whole question by officers concerned of this Department,
                    the Navy Department, and the War Department, before a final decision is
                    made.</p>
                <p>In 1932, there was held on a Sunday, at the White House, an emergency conference,
                    a decision was arrived at, and within a very short time reenforcements were on
                    their way to Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tanley</hi>] K. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >ornbeck</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
